There is not a way to do what you want just using XML AFAIK. Given a total height for the three _ImageViews_, you will need to calculate a common width that will let each _ImageView_ maintain the aspect ratio of its drawable.

You can get the aspect ratio of a drawable as follows:

    val ratioTop = ContextCompat.getDrawable(requireContext(), R.drawable.top_frame)!!.run {
        intrinsicWidth.toFloat() / intrinsicHeight
    }

You can do the same to calculate the aspect ratios of the middle and bottom views.

Given the aspect ratios and the total height, calculate the new width (w) of all the _ImageViews_ as follows:

&gt;r is aspect ratio, w is width, h is height&lt;br&gt;
r1 = w1/h1, r2 = w2/h2, r3 = w3/h2, h = h1 + h2 + h2&lt;br&gt;
set w1, w2, w3 = w so h1 = w/r1, h2 = w/r2, h3 = w/r3&lt;br&gt;
w = h/(1/r1 + 1/r2 + 1/r3)

Given this common width for the _ImageViews_, calculate the new height as follows:

    height = (w / ratioTop).toInt()

Do the same for the middle and bottom views. You will have to wait for an initial layout to get the value of `h`, so use a layout or global layout listener for this code.

Set the width and height of each view to the appropriate values and request a layout.

If you have padding/margins, you will need to make adjustments to accommodate them.

